+{"id":"br-r37-c1-rnxtc","title":"parity: dag colliders/has_cycle/v_structures + structuralholes mutual_weight wrappers (5 functions)","description":"Five missing nx wrappers across two domains. DAG (causal graph helpers): colliders(G), has_cycle(G), v_structures(G). Structural holes (Burt 1992 weight helpers): mutual_weight(G, u, v, weight=None), normalized_mutual_weight(G, u, v, norm=sum, weight=None). Add Python wrappers in __init__.py via _call_networkx_for_parity (top-level nx exports both directly), export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T20:27:40.051603203Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T20:44:40.729217982Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T20:44:40.727284532Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 674c3fc: 5 wrappers (has_cycle/colliders/v_structures/mutual_weight/normalized_mutual_weight) all verified against nx on DAG, Bayesian-net DAG, and weighted bidirectional DiGraph.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-sgjko","title":"parity: time-respecting isomorphism matchers missing","description":"NetworkX exposes TimeRespectingGraphMatcher(G1, G2, temporal_attribute_name, delta) and TimeRespectingDiGraphMatcher(G1, G2, temporal_attribute_name, delta). FrankenNetworkX does not export these classes, leaving temporal VF2 matcher API unavailable. Add wrappers that convert FrankenNetworkX graph objects via _networkx_graph_for_parity and delegate to NetworkX, plus parity tests for signatures and isomorphism mappings on temporal graph/digraph paths.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:31:58.717555427Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:35:34.565138940Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:35:34.563236879Z","close_reason":"Completed in 739ccaa","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-vw7p2","title":"parity: connectivity is_locally_k_edge_connected missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.connectivity.is_locally_k_edge_connected(G, s, t, k) tests local k-edge-connectivity between s and t. Not exposed by franken_networkx. Add Python wrapper delegating to networkx and export at top-level.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T11:51:45.929293966Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T13:04:46.859016482Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T13:04:46.857171079Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 4eb0d6d: is_locally_k_edge_connected verified P5/K4","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-wpydo","title":"parity: community leiden_communities + leiden_partitions missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.community.leiden_communities(G, ...) and leiden_partitions(G, ...) (Leiden community detection algorithm) not exposed by franken_networkx. Add Python wrappers delegating to nx.algorithms.community via _call_networkx_community_for_parity. Export both at top-level and include in __all__ under community detection section.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T12:06:41.073069778Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T13:05:29.824008425Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T13:05:29.822140820Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 4eb0d6d: leiden_communities/partitions wrappers; mirrors nx NotImplementedError parity","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-xditv","title":"parity: fruchterman_reingold_layout numeric parity with networkx","description":"fnx.fruchterman_reingold_layout / spring_layout share signatures with nx but numeric outputs are not pinned to nx for the same seed and graph. Add a parity test (tests/python/test_layout_parity.py) that builds a small fixed graph (path_graph(6), complete_graph(5), karate_club_graph), seeds with seed=42, and compares fnx vs nx node positions within tolerance 1e-6. If divergence, route to nx via _call_networkx_for_parity when method='auto' to preserve drop-in behavior.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T06:14:51.495203398Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T06:18:38.622702670Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T06:18:38.620786474Z","close_reason":"Completed in 82fb1eb","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-ygr0e","title":"parity: node_classification harmonic_function + local_and_global_consistency wrappers (2 functions)","description":"networkx.algorithms.node_classification exposes two label-propagation classifiers that franken_networkx does not surface: harmonic_function(G, max_iter=30, label_name=label) and local_and_global_consistency(G, alpha=0.99, max_iter=30, label_name=label). Both are graph-based semi-supervised learning algorithms. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py via _call_networkx_submodule_for_parity(algorithms.node_classification, ...), export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T20:49:44.313573017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T20:54:49.490059541Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-zud42","title":"parity: community louvain_partitions missing (exposes per-level Louvain hierarchy)","description":"networkx.algorithms.community.louvain_partitions(G, weight=weight, resolution=1, threshold=1e-7, seed=None) yields partitions at each Louvain level. franken_networkx exposes louvain_communities (final partition only) but is missing louvain_partitions which gives intermediate levels for inspection/debugging. Add Python wrapper delegating via _call_networkx_community_for_parity, export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T13:47:44.957693619Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T14:22:43.059355524Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T14:22:43.057527854Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 9b2ff10: louvain_partitions wrapper; verified karate seed=42 -> 2 levels, partition contents identical to nx","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r38-c1-01","title":"REVIEW: [HIGH] signature mismatches blocked nx drop-in kwarg calls (8 functions)","description":"A signature sweep comparing every fnx public function against its networkx counterpart surfaced real drop-in breakage. Missing nx-style kwargs caused TypeErrors on documented calls:

- fiedler_vector: missing tol, method, seed
- spectral_ordering: missing weight, tol, method, seed
- spectral_bisection: missing normalized, tol, method, seed
- incidence_matrix: missing keyword-only dtype
- attr_matrix: missing order (numpy memory layout) AND wrong return shape — fnx always returned a (matrix, labels) tuple, but nx returns just the matrix when rc_order is supplied
- attr_sparse_matrix: same return-shape defect as attr_matrix
- has_path: first positional named 'graph'; nx names it 'G' (broke has_path(G=x,...))
- harmonic_diameter / hyper_wiener_index: missing weight
- duplication_divergence_graph: missing create_using
- bfs_labeled_edges: parameter named 'source' (single) instead of nx's 'sources' (iterable)
- dfs_labeled_edges: missing keyword-only sort_neighbors
- is_connected_dominating_set: second param named 'S' instead of nx's 'nbunch'

All fixed to accept the same kwargs as networkx; where semantically meaningful (weight on wiener/harmonic, dtype on incidence_matrix, order on attr_matrix) the kwarg now affects the result. Others (tol/method/seed on the dense spectral solvers) are accepted for signature parity and noted as ignored by the deterministic numpy.linalg.eigh path.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed signatures + return shapes. Verified each fixed function with nx-style kwargs; existing parity tests still pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r38-c1-02","title":"REVIEW: [HIGH] to_prufer_sequence panicked (Rust) on non-tree / bad labels instead of raising NotATree","description":"fnx.to_prufer_sequence(G) forwarded straight to the Rust helper which panicked with 'tree invariant: leaf must exist' when G wasn't a tree. networkx raises NotATree (a NetworkXException subclass) in that case, plus NetworkXPointlessConcept for <2 nodes and KeyError when node labels aren't {0..n-1}. PanicException bypasses ordinary except blocks in user code. Fixed by validating is_directed / node count / is_tree / node labels in Python before calling into Rust, matching nx's exception contract exactly.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: validate in Python, raise NetworkXPointlessConcept / NotATree / KeyError as appropriate; verified on karate_club_graph, empty graph, and string-labelled trees — all raise the same exception types as nx.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
